e manual for your unit.";i:11;s:153:"But basically assuming the belt is attached with enough slack removed the tensioner bolt should be able to taske up the rest of the slack once tightened.";i:12;s:81:"Keep turning the outside nut until it is completely tight against the inside nut.";i:13;s:130:"Test your efforts - Once you have tightened the chain plug the garage door opener back into its receptacle and test its operation.";i:14;s:113:"If you have tightened the chain properly you should notice a dramatic reduction in noise and looseness of travel.";i:15;s:82:"Its hard to say exactly how long a belt drive garage door opener is going to last.";i:16;s:114:"A generalization is that any garage door opener will last between 10 and 15 years and its no exception for a belt.";i:17;s:47:"In fact belts typically last longer than chain.";i:18;s:66:"This is because the friction of the chain wears it down over time.";i:19;s:69:"Whilst caulking the gap between the door frame and the garage itself.";i:20;s:145:"Lastly you can add weather guard strips to the bottom of the garage doors and one on the inside of the garage door to form a good air tight seal.";i:21;s:63:"You might recognize this from high quality waterproof clothing.";i:22;s:105:"Most experts consider belt drive systems to be superior and there are many quality products in this line.";i:23;s:100:"A belt drive garage door opener uses a rubber belt instead of a metal chain to open the garage door.";i:24;s:69:"Because of this the system is much quieter than a chain drive system.";i:25;s:70:"These systems do tend to cost a bit more than the alternative however.";i:26;s:85:"It will be too tight if the door goes more than halfway without any added assistance.";i:27;s:31:"You then open the door by hand.";i:28;s:84:"Take a 24 brace which goes vertically into the outer edge of the door via a handsaw.";i:29;s:75:"Then position the brace in that place at the outer edge of the garage door.";i:30;s:28:"Open the door fully by hand.