he holes around the perimeter of the spring.";i:50;s:71:"Then insert another rod into a hole below the rod you already inserted.";i:51;s:70:"Tim The belt needs to be loosened at the trolley with the door closed.";i:52;s:78:"Next jump the belt at the sprocket pulley at the opener 2 notches on the belt.";i:53;s:57:"This would reduce the slack and less tension on the belt.";i:54;s:66:"The belt should still have a little slack when the door is closed.";i:55;s:51:"However you may have to adjust the travel slightly.";i:56;s:55:"How Tight Should The Chain Be On My Garage Door Opener.";i:57;s:37:"Posted on April 2 2021 by Bandi Ruma.";i:58;s:167:"Should you replace your garage door should you replace your garage door side mounted wall specialty garage door opener installation how to adjust a garage door spring.";i:59;s:36:"Garage Door Opener Chain Adjustment.";i:60;s:39:"Garage Door Chain Too Loose Long To Be.";}}